    <h2>Learn About Hobbies and Interests</h2>
    <p>In this unit, we will explore hobbies and activities that people enjoy in their free time. You will learn how to talk about your hobbies, ask others about their interests, and describe things you like to do.</p>

    <h3>Key Vocabulary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Reading</strong> - The activity of reading books or articles.</li>
      <li><strong>Playing sports</strong> - Engaging in physical activities like football, tennis, etc.</li>
      <li><strong>Cooking</strong> - Preparing food in the kitchen.</li>
      <li><strong>Drawing</strong> - Creating pictures using a pen, pencil, or other tools.</li>
      <li><strong>Watching TV</strong> - Viewing television shows or movies.</li>
      <li><strong>Listening to music</strong> - Enjoying music with headphones or speakers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Common Expressions for Hobbies</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>I like to...</strong> - Used to describe things you enjoy doing (e.g., "I like to read.").</li>
      <li><strong>I enjoy...</strong> - Another way to express liking something (e.g., "I enjoy cooking.").</li>
      <li><strong>My favorite hobby is...</strong> - Used to talk about your favorite activity.</li>
      <li><strong>What are your hobbies?</strong> - A question to ask someone about their interests.</li>
      <li><strong>Do you like...</strong> - A question to ask if someone enjoys an activity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Grammar Focus</h3>
    <p>In this unit, we will focus on the verb <strong>like</strong> and the use of hobbies in the present simple tense. The verb "like" is commonly used when talking about things we enjoy. Here are some examples:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>I like</strong> playing football. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>You like</strong> reading books. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>He/She likes</strong> watching movies. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>Do you</strong> like listening to music? (question)</li>
      <li><strong>Yes, I do</strong>. (positive response)</li>
      <li><strong>No, I don't</strong>. (negative response)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Extra Practice</h3>
    <p>For extra practice, ask a classmate about their hobbies and interests. You can also write a paragraph describing your favorite hobbies in English!</p>
